D.q[1630] = "Thank you! As my mother used to say: If you eat some Blujely and Redjely, never eat 3 Greenjely at the same time!";
D.q[6515] = "Ow! That hurts! You\'re crazy! And all that because you don\'t want to take the Kamas from me.";
D.q[6665] = "Listen to me carefully, what I\'m about to say is for your ears only. No one else can find out because I\'m risking my life and you your head, understand? Go and see Oto Mustam, in the Brakmarian Militia, tell him I sent you.";
D.q[6666] = "I didn\'t think your rat face looked familiar. Welcome to the Brakmarian Militia, you\'ll suffer but your enemies will suffer more. Thank Snori Nairb for me, and tell him he\'ll be paid as agreed. Actually, don\'t bother thanking him, just tell him he needs to send me a few more people if he wants to see his purse grow.\nDon\'t forget to come back here, I\'ve a few tasks for you and I don\'t want to involve any of the other militiamen.";
D.q[5600] = "";
D.q[4549] = "I already know, a parcel from Astrub has just arrived. Just after your defeat, the Astrub mercenaries intervened because of the ruckus caused by the fight and they arrested the Brakmarians. Magus Ax retrieved the Fogornleg Horn and sent it to us, saying that you refused to give it to the Brakmarians and were prepared to die defending it. When I think of all the trouble we\'ve gone through to obtain this horn... It will teach us not to put our faith in rumours and legends. If it\'s any consolation, there will be fewer young recruits on potato peeling duty thanks to the power of this Horn. You have served Bonta brilliantly and your loyalty is worth more to me than some magic object.";
D.q[1286] = "I\'m Captain Essacarf, the warder here in the militia prison.\nNo matter how close I watch them, Brakmarians never fail to escape at the first opportunity...";
D.q[4710] = "Well, like every morning, I prepared my things and put them in my Gobball-leather bag and the document was not there. I worked my shift near the Farmers\' Market until evening. After that I went to the Smiths\' Workshop to get a new weapon, then to the Shoemakers\' Workshop to change my boots before heading over to Atyu Sirvis\' Inn.";
D.q[4620] = "Back already? Did Magus Ax give you any information about the horn?";
D.q[2644] = "*Oops* Poochan!\nHe... Hello";
D.q[585] = "Bad, me need 4 different shells. Come back when have them.";
D.q[6170] = "You\'re not as stupid as you look, are you. Would you be interested in joining the ranks of the defenders of Brakmar? If so, I can offer you a purse full of Kamas and teach you a few veteran tricks that\'ll be of great use in a fight.\nSo, what do you say?";
D.q[6604] = "I hope no one followed you here. You\'ll have to stop coming to see me every time you have a question, people will talk. \nSo you want to know the rounds of the Brakmarian patrols, huh? There\'s a hidden office in the militia dormitory and inside, Oto Mustam keeps his documents. If you manage to get in, you\'ll find what you\'re looking for and maybe even more. Good luck.";
D.q[4245] = "Bad Evening!";
D.q[6489] = "I really don\'t have a clue where the poison is stored, but go ask Rekojel - he\'s a rebellious Ecaflip who often hangs around near the handyman workshop. If you do go pay him a visit, just watch your wallet, that area is one of the worst in all of Brakmar.";
D.q[6531] = "I detest these bandits. They\'re bad for business... especially MY business. We taught them a lesson this time. Thanks for being so... impartial. Show Amayiro this brooch to show him how grateful I am. It\'s not worth a penny, so he\'ll probably give it back to me soon enough.";
D.q[4909] = "Bahhhh.... Baaaaa... Baaaaaa... I said BAAA!";
D.q[6251] = "Nice work. I\'m going to put her in stir for the moment. In the meantime I want to find another Brakmarian to guard one of our hideouts in the handyman quarter. I\'d rather you picked someone who wasn\'t a total beginner. When you\'ve found someone suitable, bring him to me.";
D.q[1407] = "I used to find Brakmarian justice hilarious... the cruel excess, the sadistic sentences. Today, funnily enough, I\'m no longer amused.";
D.q[5605] = "";
D.q[7357] = "";
D.q[550] = "Hello dear guest! Welcome to beautiful Moon Island.\nThe agency sent me to greet you and show you the different activities we offer here.";
D.q[4621] = "Congratulations on your victory against the Brakmarians. When I think of all the trouble we\'ve gone through to get this Horn... It will teach us not to put our faith in rumours and legends. If it\'s of any consolation, you can comfort yourself with the fact that thanks to the power of this Horn, there will be fewer young recruits on potato peeling duty. You have served Bonta brilliantly and your loyalty is worth more to me than some magic object.";
D.q[3616] = "You find Pinkgob.";
D.q[6508] = "ahahahahahhaahahah\nHAHAHAHAHHARHARHARHHAA!\nI\'m laughing because you\'ve just lost 1,000 Kamas.\nHahahhahaaahahaaahaha\nHARHARHAHARHARHAAHA!";
D.q[6509] = "ahahahahahhaahahah\nHAHAHAHAHHARHARHARHHAA!\nThe old owner of the Burnt Cat Inn used to have a gaming room, and despite what he says, it\'s still in use.\nHahahhahaaahahaaahaha\nHARHARHAHARHARHAAHA!";
D.q[6255] = "Captain Starky is the chief of the Bontarian cavalry. He\'s a hot head who has lead devastating charges against us time and again. He would have been an excellent Brakmarian soldier, if he had not decided to side with the losers. I think I\'ll offer him a job in the militia anyway when Bonta is nothing more than a wasteland.";
D.q[1648] = "Hello! This is the Trool Token Exchange Stand. I can exchange your precious, hard-won Trool tokens for various items. \n\n";
D.q[4676] = "The Brakmarians serve demons. Blessed is Jiva for protecting us from them. All the same, experience has told me time and again that you have to watch out for those demons, they corrupt all that they touch. Unfortunately neither courage nor cunning will defeat them, so I\'ve decided to increase the magical powers of our armies, by giving them more spells. Since I\'m so generous, I\'ve decided to share this idea with you so that you too can profit from the success of this mission.";
D.q[1657] = "The Prism has been destroyed recently and it hasn\'t been repaired yet.";
D.q[1251] = "Brakmarian cloaks? Every tailor knows how to make them, 1 Dark Dye, 1 Black Gobbly Wool, 1 Chafer Bone... and it\'s done!";
D.q[5609] = "That wasn\'t everything, but I\'m absolutely knackered now, so I\'m going to have a little nap - wake me up if you need to.";
D.q[573] = "Recently, a tourist guide from a travel agency landed on the beach, hahaha! A wannabe pirate is also wandering about the south of the island. I think he\'s trying to find a way to leave...hahaha!";
D.q[1653] = "The inhabitants of this village are very clever, but still they haven\'t managed to make their village impregnable.\n*Polishes her crystal ball*\nBrakmar\'s troops control the village for the moment, but maybe not for long...";
D.q[3719] = "Ahhh, thank you, thank you... the nymphets will be grateful.";
D.q[6701] = "Cheep. Cheeeeeeeeeep. Hic!";
D.q[6385] = "Thewe\'s one pawt of Eltuwt\'s body that he can\'t weach. No, not thewe, I\'m talking about his back. His awms awe too small and his shell is too big fow him to weach awound and scwatch his back, and telekinesis is no use. I don\'t know what you want fwom Eltuwt, but now you know that, you have an advantage ovew him.";
D.q[569] = "Hahahaha! Another one of that travel agency\'s \"tourists for life\", eh? Well, to keep you busy, the island hides some... special attractions. Hahaha! Why don\'t you go and ask the guide who made such an explosive arrival on the beach, haha! Anyway, if you want to visit the depths of the island you\'ll have to pay. Ohohoh!";
D.q[6749] = "The others arrived in Astrub without difficulty and without seeing a single bandit. Are we ever going to find these bandits?";
D.q[4551] = "Yuuummm. Very good this dish is. Some Greenjely added you have? A great chef indubitably are you. However, even with this dish, flattery nowhere will get you.";
D.q[6347] = "As you\'re so persistent, I\'ll give you a chance to convince me. I never leave this cave anymore, so it\'s rare that I meet anyone these days. The loneliness gets to me and... how can I put it... sometimes I\'d really love some company, you know? So do you think you could maybe bring me... um... a Dragobutt in Bwork Purple Leather? It would put an end to the loneliness, and while you\'re there I\'ll do my best to get the machines working again. Oh, could you also get me some Crab Tongues? Their texture is so nice to the touch. Anyway, I want 10 lovely Crab Tongues and 10 Forked Tongues while you\'re at it. I need those to test my Robo Whoop machine. It\'s not for personal use you know! Why are you looking at me like that? What else do you think I\'m going to do with a Robo Whoop? And get me 20 planks of Kaliptus Wood. Apparently their resin is a powerful aphrodisiac.... It\'s none of your business what I\'m going to do with them, just get out of here.";
D.q[4577] = "I didn\'t think it would be easy, perhaps I pushed a little too hard. In wanting to beat Brakmar I forgot the essential part. As we were unable to flatter her, we\'ll take some time to work something else out.";
D.q[5907] = "";
D.q[1062] = "Ah, it\'s for the training? Well, take this and hurry!";
D.q[6180] = "I won\'t help anyone who has sullied their honour. Come back and see me when you\'ve made amends for your dishonour.";
D.q[4547] = "The militia is ready to defend our city, but I\'d love to know how the Brakmarians are planning to attack. The sooner we find out how they\'re planning to attack the better we can organise our defence and minimise losses.";
D.q[5722] = "Hello. Was it you who Ebru Of El sent to find Dike Tarak?";
D.q[4640] = "I\'m just doing my job, nothing more. I\'m just here on work experience. It was either this or cleaning the toilets at the Trool Fair. I didn\'t have to think about it for long.\nThe documents? I gave them back to Larry Poller, in front of the Tower of Bonta, my superior came by and picked them up later.";
D.q[6825] = "What makes you think that I mix with these people? We do not have the same values, that is for certain.";
D.q[3319] = "Thanks. Here you go.";
D.q[2538] = "Because Grandapan has one foot on Pandala and the other one in the kingdom of the gods!";
D.q[4480] = "I just got an interesting letter from our new friend Xephires. A convoy of weapons destined for Bontarian officers is on route to the city at this very moment. We have to intercept and pillage it at all costs. All my Imps are busy burgling wood from the Bonnies\' house, so you\'ll have to recruit some companions to attack the convoy. It doesn\'t matter if they\'re Brakmarian or not. According to Xephires\' letter, this convoy is well guarded so you\'ll need to round up a good force if you want to succeed. Bring whatever you steal to Stampitor on the top floor.";
D.q[5453] = "What rank do you wish to have in the militia?";
D.q[6637] = "Because I\'m telling you that they\'re as white as the mane of an abominable snowman.";
D.q[4334] = "Oh, what a marvel. And if I accept everything in this letter it could be mine? \nHm, betraying Bonta for Brakmar... I really shouldn\'t... but... it\'s such a shiny jewel.\n...\nI need some time to think. My stay in Pandala is almost at an end, but there\'s one more thing I\'ve to sort out. Maybe you could take care of it for me, as a sign of goodwill. I\'ve to deliver this box to Counsellor Boyowa. When you\'re done, Meet me in the Tower of Bonta, where you found the torn up piece of letter. After you\'ve done all that, I\'ll tell you my decision.";
D.q[5906] = "";
D.q[3316] = "Thanks. This is for you.";
D.q[4499] = "Someone spoke to you about him? Listen, I really don\'t want to get mixed up in your stories or get a friend of mine involved. I know Bonta wants to protect the world from the evil influence of Brakmar, but I\'m still not convinced enough to help you.";
D.q[655] = "Forgive me, I didn\'t get your intentions. Please accept that recipe by way of apology :\nForgetfulness of Intimidation : 4 Bloody Flints, 50 Flints, 25 Swords of the Powerful Knight, 40 Silvers.";
D.q[4579] = "Pnj(938) et Message(4578)";
D.q[6826] = "You wouldn\'t do that, would you? Yes, you would?\nOkay, I\'ll tell you what I know, but you must promise not to tell my parents.\nOne of the Ecaflips who often comes here at night sometimes talks with a Sram. Recognising this Ecaflip isn\'t difficult: each time he comes here, he prepares himself slices of Farle\'s Pig. If you arrive early enough you can\'t miss him, unless he\'s not there.";
D.q[4835] = "Pnj(987) et Message(4834)";
D.q[4876] = "Pnj(992) et Message(4875)";
D.q[4956] = "Pnj(997) et Message(4955)";
D.q[5038] = "Pnj(997) et Message(4972)";
D.q[6314] = "I wouldn\'t say no... and I\'ve just finished my bottle. You really came at the right time! *Hic* What would really make me happy would be a beer from the Bagrutte inn, that always reminds me of the good times. *Hic* Actually, bring me back two.. No, five. Ahh, what they hey, make it ten. That should do it.";
D.q[6179] = "I\'m really sorry but I\'m under strict instructions. Categorically forbidden to recruit for the Brakmarian or Bontarian militia. *whispers* I can get around this restriction when someone wants to join the minority alignment, don\'t forget...";
D.q[6778] = "Put that next to the table. This won\'t take long. \nI hope you weren\'t seen at least!? Ahh, I\'ll find some excuse if you were... bad excuses in Brakmar are two a penny!\nSpeaking of which, have you seen my sister lately? I haven\'t heard from her for a long while, but I heard that things were going well for her. It\'s not that I\'m complaining... on the contrary. I mean, it\'s not like I\'m overwhelmed with orders or anything, but I do alright. I\'ve enough business to pay the bills. \nOk, all done! I fixed the mangers so they\'d feed the Dragoturkeys with the aubergines without anyone noticing. Go put it in a public paddock... and wait for sparks to fly!!!";
D.q[6838] = "Meeeeooow.";
D.q[3460] = "I\'d like you to tell me if the Bworks still live in their village and if the legend is true.";
D.q[1376] = "I see, I see...Could you wait a moment please...Ok.\nIt seems that the magmatic mass is actually moving, but in a totally chaotic way. Therefore, Brakmar has a very small chance of being buried beneath lava. But I\'d still like to know what causes these disruptions... I\'ll stay here for a while. Here is the report you asked for.";
D.q[1596] = "Bhat bo you want buman ? How bo you bare to bisturb this bame?";
D.q[4041] = "Bewawe! The monstew is coming back!";
D.q[6561] = "Let me think. What could I ask you to do...\nFor a start, I want you to bring me some pre-cooked meals. I\'m tired of eating the Boowolf\'s leftovers. I want fish, not too well done, and certainly not fried, 5 good quality, sliced Gudgeons - that should do the trick. To drink... I\'ll take a beer that tastes like ammonia and smells like fried pig skin, like the stuff you find in Brakmar. Bring me all that, let me know I can trust you. I\'ll think about your plight while you\'re gone.";
D.q[4632] = "If I understand you correctly, you\'re telling me a hermit turtle is standing up to the will of Brakmar? This turtle is beginning to get right on my wick end! Don\'t tell me I\'m going to have to mobilize all the city\'s troops for this damned reptile!\nAttacking it won\'t work and poisoning it didn\'t result in anything, so we need to find something else, but what?";
D.q[5524] = "If serving Brakmar is your bag, I can arrange the papers to affiliate you to their militia. That\'ll save me some time and it won\'t cost you a penny. \nWhy am I doing all this, you ask. Well, Brakmar gives me a few perks for every new recruit I send their way. \nHowever, I suggest you go see Snori Nairb in Astrub before you join the alignment, he rewards anyone who wishes to enrol.";
D.q[4462] = "You bought his allegiance to our cause!? Good thinking, very Brakmarian. I\'ll make sure he\'s sent back to Bonta so he can sabotage their militia! 50,000 Kamas? Here\'s a refund... plus a finder\'s fee!\nYou\'ve got nothing to do? Good, you can go back to Bonta and find out the secret to taming Whitish Fangs. If you don\'t know where to start, why not go to the library first?";
D.q[3906] = "Come back when you know more about it. I can\'t do a thing without proof.";
D.q[5819] = "You again? What do you want this time?";
D.q[3151] = "I wouldn\'t mind teaching you how to do the little jobs but King Allister ordered some new drinking troughs for his mounts and I\'m up to my eyes with work!\nIf you can bring me back 20 Ash planks and 15 Maple planks, I\'ll find some time to teach you the basic principles of the profession.";
D.q[7145] = "Ah, well done, you managed to get rid of them! It would appear that they were supposed to deliver the documents to a guard at the foot of the Tower of Brakmar. Could you go in their place and hand over some false documents? That\'d really be killing two birds with one stone.";
D.q[6551] = "You say our militia was defeated because their equipment was inferior to the Brakmarians\'? That\'s unacceptable. Are we or are we not the most powerful city in the World of Twelve?\nI\'m going to have a word or two to Amayiro about this. You may go.";
D.q[5914] = "";
D.q[5729] = "I\'m sorry, I do not know. And even if I did, I wouldn\'t tell a stranger.";
D.q[6828] = "I\'m getting rather tired of your story about owls. If you\'re not here to gamble or to watch these Tofus being slaughtered, there\'s nothing for you here. So let the honest people have some fun in peace.";
D.q[6611] = "You\'re an honour to your uniform and to our city. Here\'s 2,000 Kamas for you, you deserve them. \nThe pictures in this old spellbook are highly obscene. I reckon there must be some horrific spells in here, we should be able use them to crush Brakmar once and for all. \nI\'m going to take the doll too, she may prove useful and in any case, you have no need for it. If I need you again, I\'ll give you a call. You may leave now.";
D.q[6211] = "Have you seen me? What kind of a pole do you take me for?\nBut wait... Don\'t you find that it smells of Brakmarian all of a sudden?";
D.q[4603] = "The ritual was a success. I made a note of the details on a parchment. I\'ve signed and dated it so Amayiro can see it\'s authentic. Good luck for the next part of your mission, you\'re going to need it.";
D.q[3428] = "Blinded by victory, danger can no longer be seen.";
D.q[5915] = "";
D.q[5916] = "";
D.q[1207] = "Me? Follow you? Sorry but I can\'t... It\'s all way too recent...\nBut take my badge, it should be enough!";
D.q[1444] = "Ah, everything is finally back to normal! I\'m still not grateful, though, you were way too slow!";
D.q[4595] = "The documents! You were able to get them back, well played! I fear Brakmar are looking for the Fogornleg Horn too, however, or why would they have stolen these documents from us? Whatever the case, we\'ve surely got a head start on them. We must make the most of it.";
D.q[605] = "Me...? Oh no, I\'m afraid of heights but I\'ve already seen other kids doing it.";
D.q[1417] = "In that case, you should bring me some Scurvion venom because our stock low... You\'ll easily find some in the Sidimote Moors.\nBring me 30 pods of it.";
D.q[3559] = "You hurry find gift!";
D.q[5728] = "Ah yes, I heard two sucker... I mean two officers talking about it. They said that the statuette was guarded day and night in the Tower of Orders in Brakmar and that those incompetent Bontarian fools would never be able to recover it.";
D.q[1122] = "The city I come from is a lot more beautiful but this one is quite charming too.";
D.q[2057] = "Bloody Enutrofs! They\'ve dug in the wrong spot again and woken up an evil creature... Haaa! If such a creature was living under this city, we would have known about it long go, although... What is it they\'re hiding from us? Go back down to the underpasses. Sooner or later, we\'ll find out what\'s going on down there.";
D.q[6497] = "You\'re able to do business with the Brakmarians. That\'s certainly a surprise. I don\'t know exactly what kind of trouble is brewing, but Milone Corichel the jeweller is involved in corruption dealings. Question him for more information.";
D.q[4591] = "A Brakmarian spy managed to get into the city and some documents concerning our research into the Fogornleg Horn! He managed to get away, but our archers are sure they injured his leg. You should be able to catch up with him, he went towards Brakmar.";
D.q[3023] = "In this case, I can\'t do anything for you. Your spirit isn\'t ready. You\'re not worthy. I\'m not even sure you smell nice. Go back to your god, or go see one of his disciples. A Xelor should be able to inform you.";
D.q[3761] = "Bloody scarecrows, they never stop moving about. They know that young adventurers come here to practice their fighting skills. The inexperienced fighters can\'t hurt them, so the scarecrows play hide and seek for laughs. I\'d be better off with a pitchfork than this big bloody pike here. I\'d make a fine haystack out of these straw puppets.";
D.q[6418] = "Even during your mission you were thinking of your boss. You deserve a little bonus. As for me, I\'m going to give this potion to Sbab.\nWhy Sbab? It\'s none of your business, keep your nose out.";
D.q[1048] = "Only ten pods? The militia is really squeamish, if we want to exterminate Brakmar one day, there\'ll have to be one heck of a row!\nAnyway, since you\'ve been sent by the militia, you have a 50% discount, so that makes 20,000 Kamas...";
D.q[6829] = "I once knew someone stickier than you, it was a young jelly that fell in love with the sole of a militiaman\'s boot. The only way for the militiaman to get rid of it was to kill it with fire. I don\'t suppose you want to suffer the same fate, though, do you?\nObviously not, so I invite you to go home and let us entertain ourselves in peace.";
D.q[4624] = "Don\'t hesitate to use threats if necessary. The tavern keepers are easily convinced.";
D.q[5921] = "";
D.q[4472] = "Bontarian smiths are not skilled enough to make this type of equipment. That means that Bonta hired a smith to forge all this stuff.\nYou must find this smith and convince him to work for us.";
D.q[2149] = "Pnj(495) et Message(2148)";
D.q[1841] = "Beautiful! An Acrimonious Eriaxis Rigida, haha! A beautiful specimen. Hold your ears up to this fellow\'s petals and you\'ll be in a bad mood all day! Ah! I lost track of time! I\'ve to feed my plant Audrey, she\'s an extremely rare acid Brakmaris... Could you give me a hand and water it for me?";
D.q[2258] = "Unlike us Fecas, these stupid creatures aren\'t known for their intelligence! Well... that\'s it... a Gobball\'s gone missing: would you mind looking for it? I think it went over near the underpasses. Go and see Gasdaure, if anyone knows where it is, it\'s her.";
D.q[3726] = "Bow down before the almighty Iop, protector of Amakna. Admire his sword, symbol of all his power.";
D.q[7434] = "";
D.q[3945] = "Ah, you\'ve got the recipe, good! Can you go and collect the ingredients now?";
D.q[5936] = "";
D.q[6777] = "A letter for me?! Let\'s see what your master wants now.\nDear Fidji Merline... blah blah blah blah... tens of thousands of Kamas... yada yada yada... a bonus for your sister... bada bing bada boom... \nVery well. I usually side step the Bonta/Brakmar conflict, but this time I\'m gonna lend a hand. Go bring me 4 Mangers in Cherry Wood and 40 Aubergines. I\'ll give you further instructions afterwards.";
D.q[7435] = "";
D.q[1864] = "I think I\'m going craaaazy. My house was across the road there when I went for a long walk over to Brakmar one evening, okay, and when I came back, poof, the place is gone. How can a house just disappear? SO who dunnit? Me? Him? That dog over there? You? Come to think of it, you do look a bit dodgy. Hmmmm...";
D.q[6383] = "Oh, I see you have alweady embwaced the dawk side. A vewy good choice. While Bonta buwns, you\'ll wealise that youw dweams awe within weach and no one will be able to stop you fwom wealising them.";
D.q[7961] = "He also has the biggest Dragoturkey enclosure on the whole island. Yes, it\'s true.\nBy the way, what do you think of my snowmonster? Don\'t say anything silly, or I\'ll tell Bébert.";
D.q[4477] = "Brakmar? You come from... BRAKMAR?\n*Grabs a weapon*\nGet out! I know you\'re just sweetening me up so you can plant a dagger in my side! Get out!";
D.q[3032] = "Brakmar and its tadpole army fled once again when facing the courageous warriors of Bonta. Enlist in Bonta and you\'ll always be a winner!";
D.q[7964] = "I\'m going to tell you where to find each snowmonster. Then you go and look at them and say which one is scariest. It\'s so easy even a Iop could do it!";
D.q[3715] = "Indeed. Pouring their bath water on your wounds will heal them. People from all around come to this magical place to heal their battle scars... I\'ve to fill the basins all the time.";
D.q[7436] = "";
D.q[5504] = "Brakmarians..! Here..?! If you think you can stop me, fiends, you\'ve got another think coming.";
D.q[2171] = "Pnj(475) et Message(1965)";
D.q[6387] = "Where\'s my head at? I even forgot to give them back to him the last time we spent the night together... anyway, that doesn\'t concern you. Here are the keys. Tell him that next time I\'ll remember to give them back to him before he has to send someone to remind me, he\'s very grumpy sometimes.";
D.q[3608] = "Are you finished dear? I hope so, since you\'re over here speaking to me! Ahh, this work is good, very good. If you have time to do some more odd jobs for me, please come over, but remember, I don\'t provide materials. That\'s up to you.";
D.q[551] = "But dear guest, it was specified in the contract that it was a one-way ticket. The return journey wasn\'t part of the special offer. You should have paid the extra fee or chosen another destination.";
D.q[3964] = "Did you bring me the Kamas or what?";
D.q[3246] = "Y..Y...You\'re hard of understandin\' aren\'t you? I\'ll make it simpler and clearer. You use a listing rune. You equip your craftsman tool and you ap...ap...appear on the list! You unequip your tool and you\'re no longer on the list. When you\'re on the l...l...list, everybody can see you. You get it now?";
D.q[5486] = "*blushes*\nDirty flatterer.";
D.q[4197] = "Hello! I\'m Muleze, the lab keeper. I used to work here as an alchemist until Otomai lost control of the experiment he was doing and gave up. We used to breed one of the most shocking of creatures: the Tynril.\nThis creature can duplicate according to his moods but isn\'t too dangerous. However it\'s a wild, and its behaviour is difficult to predict.";
D.q[3375] = "Yes! You have done well young one. I\'m impressed... but it\'s not over yet. Here is the key that will lead you to your next challenge.";
D.q[3575] = "Yes. I like courageous and powerful warriors. I\'m myself quite courageous, I\'m not scared of these horrible slimy, creeping, crawling, glistening and dirty creatures prowling around here. I\'ll personally reward your enthusiasm. Bring it on!";
D.q[4235] = "In this impenetrable cage, draped in chains, lived Otomai\'s greatest creation, the very jewel of the land whose name represents both its voracity and its strength. Who could have imagined that an insignificant pinhead of matter could give rise to this... Titan.";
D.q[7446] = "";
D.q[303] = "But this gumshoe...";
D.q[6395] = "To make a back-scratcher, you need to start with an incomplete back-scratcher. One you\'ve got the incomplete back-scratcher, stand in front of the forge and we\'ll finish it together.";
D.q[5932] = "";
D.q[5657] = "But what\'s happening to me? I\'ve lost control of my body.\nWhy am I hopping around like an idiot? What\'s happened to my hair? Why do I now have a mohican? My hands have taken on a life of their own, I\'m worried about punching myself... and my legs... no, no, not the slam dance!\nIt\'s a nightmare, I\'ve never felt more stupid in my life! I\'m like a scatterbrained Iop crossed with a Tofu. I\'ll be the laughing stock of Amakna!\n...\nCough... you\'ll find what you\'re looking for... cough cough... in the Crackler Mines... cough.";
D.q[4524] = "It\'s not as easy as it seems. We did everything we could with Otomai to prevent anyone from getting to close. \nFirst, we need to open this door, thanks to the slabs and to the four rooms...\nTo open this door, a team will have to be united, well-organised and know the island like the back of their hand. \nThose who succeed in opening the door, are worthy of meeting the beast.";
D.q[5666] = "So it\'s you who\'s taking care of it?\nWhat you need to capture a stubborn soul is a Cokesoul Stone. I can help you make one, but I\'ll need you to bring me some items. For the time being, just bring me 1 Lucky Soul Stone for Big Souls, 4 Bow Meow Ghosts, 4 units of Gobball Blood, 4 Aubergines and a Mojeetov Cocktail, which you can find on Otomai Island. When you\'ve brought me all that, meet me in the ritual room under the Tower of Brakmar. You can get in through a little passage between two shelves at the bottom of the south-west part of the tower. I\'ll need an Osamodas who knows the spell Natural Resistance and an alchemist who can make Phoenix Blood to help me enchant the stone.";
D.q[6394] = "To assemble the handle and the tip of the scratcher you\'ll need a handyman to stand in front of the forge. The handyman will need the following: a Handyman\'s Hammer, and 2 Ebonite in their inventory, as well as the handle and the tip, obviously.";
D.q[4666] = "What are you still doing here? The other militiamen are already attempting to hold off the Bontarians but they won\'t be able to do so for ever. Hurry up and bring me the Fogornleg Horn.";
D.q[4184] = "Do you know the Pirates of Otomai\'s Ark? These despicable creatures fire cannonballs at me whenever I fly over the ark. I\'ve already lost many Scarplanes because of them. I\'ll let you use my Scarplanes if you go kill a few of them. That should set an example to the others and quiet them down a bit.";
D.q[1311] = "But, what are you doing? You\'re trying to be nice?! But it\'s completely stup...Hemm, wait a minute... You\'re trying to wheedle me, it\'s bribery in fact! It\'s bad, really bad! Well done!";
D.q[6393] = "To carve the back-scratcher\'s handle you\'ll need a wand carver to stand in front of the forge. The wand carver will need the following: a Handle Slasher, and 2 Maple Wood in their inventory, as well as 5 Treechnid Resin.";
D.q[6658] = "May the spirit of light trapped in this hammer be driven out.\nMay the Darkness swallow up that which once belonged to the demons.\nMay the dark magic of this hammer be finally restored.";
D.q[4179] = "I now organise hunts. Modern adventurers no longer have goals. I feel I bring meaning to their life with my hunting sessions. Incidentally, it also enables me to regularly cull the creatures on the island. Otomai is against this and would rather leave nature take its course but we eventually came to an agreement and he let me beat the island\'s ecosystem with a stick provided that I send him all the results. \nDo you want to have a go at hunting?";
D.q[4128] = "What the deuce? We\'re being attacked by Pirates! \nI didn\'t even have time to throw a cannonball at them! Don\'t just stand there looking pretty, do something useful for once... Charge at the enemy and kill those bloody good-for-nothings, those Raul Mop eating, aquatic Scurvion surrender monkeys!";
D.q[3722] = "Piwi piwi piwiiiiiiiiiiiiiii!!!";
D.q[3725] = "Piwi!";
D.q[4060] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[4076] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[2773] = "Hewwo! You\'re welcome to my house. You\'ve got a spalkling eye like a stal in the night... ";
D.q[4126] = "At last! I was starting to lose my patience. Let me load the munitions onto the ship and have breakfast, and then you can come and see me when you feel ready to travel to the island.";
D.q[4141] = "Thanks to you, the Coralators will be able to use what\'s left of their brains to do useful things, like breaking shells or skimming pebbles across the water. If Otomai could see what you\'ve done for them, he would be very happy.";
D.q[5954] = "";
D.q[4636] = "Hello you. Did you find someone to make a back-scratcher? If they\'re reluctant to help you, tell them to come see me.";
D.q[1476] = "A Sniffling Staff? Out of blood, I guess. I don\'t make them anymore, but I can make you one if you want me to. But I\'ll need some Vampire Blood -about one jar for a staff, and I\'ll ask for 100 Kamas for the service. I\'ll take care of the rest of the ingredients.";
D.q[7595] = "I taught the greatest hunters of our time, and the hat that I wear was given to me by one of my former students, Mikula. \nSpeaking of hunting, how would you like to challenge one of my trophies? \nOh, did I not tell you? I have the largest collection of creature souls, even that of the famous alchemist Otomai pales into insignificance when compared to mine.";
D.q[6412] = "If that\'s the case, there\'s no point in you bringing me the skins. I\'ll give you the recipe so you can see what a real healthy salad is, not one of those diet meals, full of salt and Iop knows what else that unsavoury merchants try to flog on the marketplace.";
D.q[6036] = "";
D.q[7438] = "";
D.q[4208] = "I lost my bet. I bet that you\'d lose this fight after a few minutes. Defeating the Kimbo on his own slaying ground is a great achievement, worthy of a hero. With a bit of luck, you could take on a Gigantic Kralove or even a dragon. Otomai was right, creatures like us all have a weak point and end up being replaced. It\'s natural... irreversible evolution.\nEven you, one day you\'ll end up in the stomach of a creature who proved stronger than you. It will probably choke on your swollen head though, so you might have the last laugh after all! Take this reward. Otomai once told me that it\'s very valuable.";
D.q[2754] = "You\'re courageous. But are you intelligent enough? I challenge you to defeat another of my students. He put on his combat outfit especially for you!";
D.q[261] = "I\'m sorry, but I can still hear those filthy creatures scurrying along the floor up there. \nCome back when you\'ve got what I asked you for.";
D.q[3419] = "But they were pursued by the dreadful cousin of Orukawa who wanted to avenge for him. He bled them dry as if they were Gobballs and sold their remains as sausage meat on the markets in Brakmar. What a tragic ending!\nAnd that\'s how Yoshawa\'s rat found himself being alone. He hid in the sewers of the Castle of Amakna for many years. \nrumour has it that he met Otomaï himself, while he was testing new potions with yet unsuspected effects on turtles from Moon Island.";
D.q[3420] = "Otomaï entrusted the rat with the turtles but no one suspected that the effects of the potions given to the turtles would be transmitted to all rats...\nThat\'s how the rat grew and became humongous and even more dangerous. \nSome scientists of this world even explained this out of proportion size of the rats living in caves and sewers, thanks to the side effects of this terrible potion that are transmitted very quickly to rats after a simple bite or mating. And well, you know how rats are... almost as active as Wabbits!";
D.q[212] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[1819] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[5547] = "What? You want my picture?\nIt\'s very draughty here, and I can\'t manage to keep still... you think it\'s funny, do you?\nOn top of that, the lighting is terrible. Who was the interior designer? You\'d find better in Otomai\'s bog!";
D.q[5959] = "";
D.q[3500] = "Bworkid bring Bwork no paxifiks. You suffer, scraaaaap!!!";
D.q[3552] = "You not happy? Me call Bwork Females, you talk about tapestry work with their axes!";
D.q[6670] = "Pnj(367) et Message(4810)";
D.q[1828] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[8015] = "Well yes, I\'m with Jean-Louis. We have been married for over sixty years.\nRobert had just won a fortune but the idiot refused to buy the beautiful house by the sea I wanted, so I asked Jean-Louis to eliminate him so that we could both live together and spend the Robert\'s money as we saw fit. At the time I didn\'t know that idiot Robert had invested his fortune in the fields, and when the big freeze hit I lost everything.\nToday, Jean-Louis and I live in this little cabin and there there\'s very little left of Robert\'s fortune.\nDo you intend to betray us? I\'m sure we can come to some little arrangement...";
D.q[7437] = "";
D.q[549] = "By the Great Beaaarrd, you\'ll dooo that for me? *hic* you\'ll be my heroooo *hic* and your rewwward will be a ba...barrel *hic*.\nBriiing me whatever you want, except wa...water *hic* I\'m afraid of waaateeeer *hic* A bottle of rum will do *hic* then you can... take your reward *hic*";
D.q[4112] = "To make that key I\'ll need: 1 Stone of Aerogoburius the Malicious, 1 Stone of Aqualikros the Merciless, 1 Stone of Ignirkocropos the Famished and 1 Stone of Terraburkahl the Perfidious.";
D.q[4113] = "To make that key I\'ll need: 5 Lousy Pig Shoes, 1 First part of the Dragon Pig Maze Key, 1 Second part of the Dragon Pig Maze Key, 5 Broken Tridents and 5 Lousy Pig Ears.";
D.q[544] = "I\'m thinking of exploring the island, there\'s bound to be treasure buried somewhere. While I\'m on this expedition, I\'m going to gather loads of different things to make a raft and get out of here.";
D.q[1259] = "Bah, you don\'t even have enough Kamas.";
D.q[129] = "Bows with magic powers are rare and tricky to make, you often need to combine rare woods with precious metals and stones to make a bow that will be both magical and deadly.";
D.q[3182] = "You\'re in an incredible labyrinthine library and you may never get out of here alive. \nThis library consists of 16 small rooms which all together form a big square-shaped library. If you want to change rooms you must defeat the appropriate group of creatures. Each group will take you to a new room. There are two different groups of creatures. When you defeat a group of creatures (whichever one), they\'ll take you to the next room as a reward. Warning! Both types of creatures have their own little habits. Each of them always go in the same direction. Therefore you\'ll have to fight against different groups if don\'t want to endlessly go round and round.";
D.q[3978] = "Yes, that\'s for sule! But how can we apploach him?";
D.q[1800] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[3470] = "Trool pit that way. Trool very strong!";
D.q[5420] = "";
D.q[2756] = "You\'re courageous. But are you intelligent enough? I challenge you to defeat another of my students. He put on his combat outfit especially for you!";
D.q[4887] = "Very good, here\'s my plan: I\'m going to make the Brakmarians believe that the Fogornleg Horn has the power to cause city walls to fall down and to paralyse anyone standing in front of it when it\'s blown. The plan is almost ready but there are still a few details to iron out, and I still need your help. I need enough Miteters to make the rock crumbly and some royal jelly blubber to finish the paralysis potion that the volunteers are going to drink at the appropriate moment.";
D.q[1204] = "You\'re ready to join the Order of The Valiant Heart.\nAre you still sure of your choice ?";
D.q[6386] = "You need a special back-scratcher? No, no, I don\'t want to know what you want to do with it. Start by bringing me my keys, Fidji Merline has forgotten to give me them again.";
D.q[970] = "Captain Arlok at your service! What can I do for you?";
D.q[2552] = "If you say no, you\'re insulting me. If you\'re insulting me, you\'re insulting all the Pandawas, not mentioning our goddess... After that, it won\'t be easy to get information about the Dofus of Pandala... And isn\'t that the reason you\'re here?";
D.q[568] = "You\'re on Moon Island, your home for the next 50 years! Hahaha! Fortunately, the island has been a little livelier recently. You won\'t get bored, at least not for the first week! Hahaha!";
D.q[3992] = "You\'we stwong enough now, you can join my othew companions. But you on youw own won\'t be enough... I need mowe attendants. Go and wecwuit some mowe!";
D.q[2279] = "*mumbles*\nMay the god Iop give you vitality, may your sword squeal and be sharp, may your arm be long with Compulsion!";
D.q[543] = "Well hello there, stranger! My name\'s Kib Rock. You might not have heard of me, but one day I\'ll be a great pirate. I bought myself a talking treasure map, but I beached on this island after following its directions too closely. Sadly, I lost my main topgallant sail when I came flying through the air.";
D.q[6392] = "You were able to craft your item. It\'s not bad, but you\'re going to have to improve if you hope to beat me one day.";
D.q[847] = "Hurry and make up for your stupidity!";
D.q[305] = "Ch...Ch...Ch...Chip Endale";
D.q[7439] = "";
D.q[2604] = "Didn\'t you meet my messengel? You have to go to Telldala, intloduce youlself to the chief who often walks outside the village. Be quick!";
D.q[2582] = "...infecting the Pandawa hats with the McSheth bacteria was a brilliant idea! Plus, the wind brought other diseases to the four corners of the island: those damned adventurers might be surprised yet...";
D.q[1257] = "Ahah, why should I give you this recipe? I\'ll need at least 1,000 Kamas to loosen my tongue.";
D.q[2885] = "Nobody can get close to the receptacle, although Grandapan considers it a tourist attraction. This object attracts the fierce monsters that watch over it. Only the strongest can get into the village... as well as the Pandawas who come for their initiation ritual.";
D.q[3622] = "Weight of me in Bwork beer!";
D.q[4529] = "You\'re going to pay a little visit to Larry Poller in the Bonta Tower of Orders and ask him how we should improve our military arsenal. I\'ll mock you viciously until you come up with some concrete results.";
D.q[1294] = "You\'re lucky I had the sun in my eyes... I should have won.\nCome back again tomorrow and things won\'t go so well for you.";
D.q[5061] = "";
D.q[1690] = "Choose the number of Trool Tokens";
D.q[1694] = "Choose your prize.";
D.q[2320] = "So, you did bring the bow to Dragonsly?";
D.q[7548] = "Hello #1, I see you\'re new here. If you\'d like, I can teach you a few of this world\'s basic principles.";
D.q[5062] = "";
D.q[1249] = "*hic* Greedovore juice! *hic*\nIf you *hic* brriiing me at least 4 units of it, I\'ll make w*hic*!";
D.q[1264] = "You\'ve a funny way of encouraging dreamers!\nDon\'t you understand that my fair makes me happy? Or maybe you\'re just jealous... Anyway, here is your filled form.";
D.q[3062] = "You should be able to find anything you need around here.";
D.q[2887] = "If you\'re ready to leave, I\'ll take you to the entrance of the village.";
D.q[1291] = "Clank ClankingClank Clanclanking Clanking Clankling Clank Clanking King!";
D.q[5873] = "";
D.q[1543] = "Ha, elections! This kind of prediction is my specialty. To make my divine declarations really reliable, I need some Oni Dust.\nIt will cost you 200 Kamas and a bag of that famous dust to find out who our next steward will be.";
D.q[1589] = "Clear off now!";
D.q[5876] = "";
D.q[3001] = "You\'ve done a fantastic job with this Piwi. Wasn\'t too ferocious, was it?! (Scribbles frenetically, mumbling). Aah! How treacherous! He really doesn\'t respect anything! Raah! Here, I give you this book, it\'s now free of mistakes... Take this manual as well, I put it in your inventory, don\'t hesitate to read it through! It\'s a very useful book for young adventurers.";
D.q[3471] = "Come back and visit me when you have time. If you can help a Goblin you can certainly help a Bwork magus.";
D.q[2544] = "Hahaha! Don\'t worry... it\'s a sign of recognition between wise Lenald and I. Welcome! Now, what are you doing in this neck of the woods?";
D.q[3856] = "Female adventurers often stop by salons to get energy back, have a chat, and sip on a fresh mimilk.";
D.q[5063] = "";
D.q[5880] = "";
D.q[1959] = "Okay, here\'s what you gotta do. Go by the timber warehouse, it\'s not far, and find the entrance to his hideout. It\'s really great, it\'s like a hidden trap door. Now you\'ll have to be quiet, tippie toe on those cute little toes okay... you don\'t want his wife... I mean his enemies... you don\'t want his enemies to discover it, okay. Okay, well get your little toosh outta here honey... and hurry! Byeee!";
D.q[2187] = "There are dandelions in the fields north-east of town, if I remember rightly.";
D.q[5974] = "";
D.q[2160] = "Is a half filled jug half empty?";
D.q[731] = "A clairvoyant told me this morning that Captain Tsog had some information of paramount importance to tell me before he dies.\nFind a way to get in touch with him at the cemetery to the east of Bonta and come back to report to me his last words.\nAsk Captain Alrok if you need further information about where his grave is.";
D.q[6744] = "We\'re watching all the exits, no one can go in or out without us knowing about it.";
D.q[6420] = "Listen carefully, squirt, if you\'ve come to play games, you\'ve come to the wrong person. The last guy who talked to me like that learnt his lesson - he was out of school for two and a half weeks. You better watch it. So how about you shut your trap and change your tone of voice.";
D.q[4638] = "Good, now you understand that it\'s best not to disappoint me. In future, you\'d do well to complete the missions I give you.";
D.q[6421] = "Listen carefully, squirt, if you\'ve come to play games, you\'ve come to the wrong person. The last guy who talked to me like that learnt his lesson - he was out of school for two and a half weeks. You better watch it. So how about you shut your trap and change your tone of voice.";
D.q[6042] = "";
D.q[5981] = "";
D.q[5979] = "";
D.q[6380] = "You have chosen the path of losews, but thewe is still time to change youw mind. They fool you with illusions that you can contwol youwself bettew, the light blinds you and you don\'t know whewe you go. Wenounce now and embwace the dawkness and youw powew will be limitless. You\'ll no longer have to take owdews fwom anyone, you\'ll be youw own mastew.";
D.q[6739] = "I guess we\'re lucky after all. We\'re getting closer to where we want to be every second. And further from where we don\'t want to be!";
D.q[7440] = "";
D.q[4646] = "Huh? You\'re going to leave me here? In my state, I\'ll get caught! You wouldn\'t do that do a Brakmarian ally, surely?";
D.q[5982] = "";
D.q[2386] = "Are you sure you want to start a career as a Axe smith?";
D.q[3273] = "Come on! Come closer and try not to fall in a hole! Just watch your steps! On each slab there\'s a number. This number indicates the number of trapped slabs out of the 8 adjoining slabs. With a bit of logic, you should easily guess which slabs are trapped and which aren\'t. Those that aren\'t trapped will lead you to the other side.";
D.q[1597] = "You didn\'t reach the second level yet. \nGo back and practice with this Arachnee.";
D.q[2553] = "You\'ve proven yourself valiant! You\'re worthy... I\'ll tell you of the Dofus of Pandala... wise Lenald believes you should know. He\'s the one who sent me... Are you ready?";
D.q[7441] = "";
D.q[5984] = "";
D.q[2824] = "In a very short amount of time, you\'ve become a great Pandawa. Our goddess congratulates you. Master Lenald now fully trusts you and, as a gesture of this trust, has decided to offer you a very important mission. If you succeed you\'ll get what you want.";
D.q[4122] = "You\'ve beaten me at my own game. I can\'t believe it...\nI thought about the answer to your question all night long, and I still haven\'t found it.\nIn the meantime, you can cross the bridge.";
D.q[3290] = "Ah, so you\'ve just defeated the terrible Sponge Mob as well! \nWith a bit of luck, you\'ll think about me when you end up in the Giant Kralove\'s stomach. \nYou look pretty tense, relax! The fight\'s over, the sun\'s shining, and you\'re in Astrub! What more could you ask for?  \nMy goodness me! You\'re as stiff as a dried Kaliptus stick! \nLet me show you how to relax!";
D.q[393] = "You\'re in luck, I have the list right here. I need 90 Arachnee Legs and 65 Five-Leaf Clovers.";
D.q[6427] = "Ecaflips? Hah, didn\'t see no Ecaflips.\nWhat is an Ecaflip anyway?";
D.q[7442] = "";
D.q[6523] = "Looks like it\'s not your lucky day but I\'ll still answer your question, that way I won\'t be stuck with you all evening. You know the miners\' market? Yes, in Brakmar, of course! Petra has a bolthole near the market, that\'s all I can tell you and I don\'t want to discuss it further with you.";
D.q[5988] = "";
D.q[3483] = "Come on, let\'s try again! Hit harder this time!";
D.q[829] = "Come on, tell your master what happened.";
D.q[5401] = "";
D.q[5735] = "...";
D.q[5990] = "";
D.q[2445] = "You\'ll recognize them easily. These big stone arches are scattered all over the world. When you see one, approach it. It will remember your passing by. You\'ll then be able to teleport yourself from another Zaap in exchange of a few Kamas.";
D.q[5892] = "";
D.q[5991] = "";
D.q[2123] = "Come over here so that I can validate your quests";
D.q[1534] = "Oh, ok, don\'t let it get to you, the code to open the door is 11115555.";
D.q[2873] = "You can deposit both Kamas and items in your bank account.\nYou can only have one bank account. \nEvery time you access your bank account, even if you\'re just having a look inside, you must pay a fee.\nThis fee depends on the number of items stored in your bank account, and the number of items you can store in your bank account is determined by how long you\'ve banked with us. Each person living in the province of Amakna gets a bank account.\n\nSo, as time passes by, it will cost you more and more to access your account, as you deposit more items in it. However, the longer you stay with us, the more items you\'ll be able to put in it.";
D.q[7144] = "You\'re back from the temple? I hope you took in as much as you could, there\'s so much to do there.";
D.q[5992] = "";
D.q[2673] = "You\'d better go get some rest at the village Inn. You look exhausted from your trip across the island... and to think that it was just to bring me this flask.";
D.q[6886] = "";
D.q[2605] = "Ah! My bamboo! I\'ll be able to make many shields thanks to you! Here, this one\'s for you!";
D.q[2690] = "I\'m the best Pandawaiian Shield Maker in the world! And I invite any of my apprentices to try to outdo me. This is the best and fastest way to progress for them as well as for me... Remember that.";
D.q[5897] = "";
D.q[4090] = "Warning! Do you really want to forget all the levels of this spell?";
D.q[5993] = "";
D.q[344] = "You can\'t become a Lumberjack if you have no passion for it. Cutting down trees all day long requires an extraordinary will. Some trees are easier to cut down than others and you\'ll need experience in wood-cutting to fell the biggest ones. You must own an axe if you want to cut a tree. I can sell you one if you want.\nI can also teach you the basics of the Lumberjack profession.";
D.q[6434] = "You have a good mind for business. If you want to find out more, get in touch with Hersa Dark Claw in Bonta, but make sure you don\'t tell her we told you!";
D.q[5900] = "";
D.q[5997] = "";
D.q[5899] = "";
D.q[5995] = "";
D.q[2314] = "Argh! You gave me a fright, ye fool! Thought you were one of those big grossewer rats... Speaking of rats, I think I got somethin\' to suit a strappin\' young thing like yourself... right up your street... Let\'s have a look here... A fine fellow!!!";
D.q[5901] = "";
D.q[3343] = "Congratulations! \n\nYou\'ve won a fantastic touristy trip to the Wabbit Jungle, sponsored by the airline company \'In Kamas\'! Safari Atmosphere Guaranteed! \n\nNo hard feelings... and enjoy your trip!";
D.q[5999] = "";
D.q[6484] = "Ohh, that\'s only a Bow Meow. If I don\'t pay attention, someone could easily come along and steal the documents... and very likely hurt me too.";
D.q[6880] = "Oh, but isn\'t mummy\'s Bow Meow a cutie! Without me, this adorable little animal would have ended up in the belly of a dangerous monster or as a ghost under the blows of a vile butcher\'s cleaver. But fortunately for him, I\'m here and I make sure he has everything he needs.\nAs an Eniripsa ,my skills come in very handy when he\'s feeling poorly, but I can also repel intruders when they come here. Nobody cares much about his health other than me. He is so cute...";
D.q[6640] = "You have ONE chance of getting out of here alive. Take it and run!";
D.q[5070] = "";
D.q[7448] = "";
D.q[1587] = "Would you like to give the ring back to me?";
D.q[6887] = "This Bow Meow wouldn\'t hurt a Moskito. It is the sweetest and kindest creature I have ever I known. I would not be surprised to learn that an Eniripsa soul was reincarnated in this furry little body.";
D.q[4001] = "I\'m way too strong for you but if you beat my best disciple, I\'ll serve your prince.";
D.q[4219] = "You shouldn\'t go there. It\'s an extremely dangerous place.\nA terrible creature has been living there for aeons and we believe that it might even have been here before the island emerged from the sea.\nIt devoured many adventurers and its appetite for flesh seems to be insatiable.";
D.q[6450] = "You have to find the key to the hideout. I guess some high-ranked bandits must have copies. When you find the key, take some militiamen or mercenaries with you and get yourself to the bandits lair... have a look around and find any document that you think might be helpful to our investigation. I\'m counting on you to use your head. Hersa, and her connections, could be very useful to you I think.";
D.q[6308] = "You\'re so ugly that even the powers of 1,000 gods could not fulfil your request.";
D.q[2935] = "Congratulations! You fought the good fight! I validate your level passage...";
D.q[5302] = "";
D.q[4789] = "I was just curious, there\'s no harm in that.";
D.q[6305] = "You\'ll find the entrance to the underground passage leading to the Well of Corrupted Souls in the East of the Bandit Territory. You can only get into the well if you\'re accompanied by at least four proven villains from Brakmar who, if they have not chosen a speciality, are ready to do so.";
D.q[5397] = "";
D.q[3583] = "Yes. Me want to be angel to fly to Bonta.";
D.q[4567] = "Hello, how do you fancy a change of scenery? I\'ve got just the thing for you. Head over to Moon Island and find the guardian of the Fogornleg Horn. If you can recover the Fogornleg Horn at the same time, so much the better.";
D.q[5303] = "";
D.q[2741] = "You\'re willing to train and I like that. But if you think I\'ll let you come to my Dojo dressed like this, you\'re mistaken! Plus, I don\'t even have proof that you\'re healthy enough. Hasn\'t anyone told you the back of your eye is bloodshot? No? Well, I\'m telling you now aren\'t I? Go find a Shamanic certificate and a proper training outfit.";
D.q[6007] = "";
D.q[5395] = "";
D.q[6263] = "What did I tell you the last time? That I didn\'t want to get mixed up in all this business.";
D.q[6889] = "You\'re talking nonsense. How could something so fragile and cute actually be evil incarnate? Twisting my mind with your poisonous words. If you try anything against this little Bow Meow, I\'ll unleash the powers of Sadida against you.";
D.q[6008] = "";
D.q[5772] = "Just how badly do you want to become neutral? With your reputation, and the amount of paperwork I\'m going to have to do as a result, it\'s going to cost you. 128,000 Kamas, to be exact. Don\'t forget though, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[3625] = "You want to trample Piwi with your hose? You give Piwi egg!";
D.q[7450] = "";
D.q[2625] = "You want my son! What the heck is going on? Why does everyone want my son?\n*in a low voice* Why is he so popular... is it because of his hair?\nI\'m sorry but my son\'s already engaged to the daughter of the Dojo\'s owner. I could never let him go again for a sum below 100,000 Kamas. ";
D.q[2783] = "I think I\'m gonna stay here for a while. Just enough time for all my friends to recover. Plus, I\'ve come across a nice shop assistant whose hair is as soft as my beard! Her eyes are like two Rubies and... she drinks more than I do! I\'m not leavin\' without tryin\' to put my pickaxe into her li\'l heart! That\'s for sure! I could even take my bag of jewels out, and that\'s something! I feel young again!";
D.q[4566] = "Your world amused me, so I\'ll keep my promise not to destroy it...for the time being.\nIf you bring me an old Bunch of Keys, I\'ll swap it for a new one. You\'ll be able to use it to confront the strongest monsters.";
D.q[6010] = "";
D.q[6213] = "You don\'t seem to understand. I can\'t say anything, got it?";
D.q[5068] = "";
D.q[5306] = "";
D.q[6014] = "";
D.q[2178] = "Could you keep it down a bit? Locette is sleeping soundly. She had a strong headache when she came back from her mission. I hope it\'s nothing serious.";
D.q[2770] = "You feel ready to pass the Sandawa level? Perfect! Every day, you\'ll have to come here to defeat a Pandawushuka Mastern in a fair fight . Beat him to prove me your value.";
D.q[6026] = "";
D.q[6015] = "";
D.q[6234] = "Thanks very much. Here, take some bread. It\'s not much, but it\'ll fill your stomach while you travel at least.\nNow show me your card, I\'ll show you where I saw the Sram.";
D.q[4790] = "Well... I... you know... I wanted to catch him red-handed... you know?";
D.q[2768] = "You feel ready to pass the Shodanwa level? If so, you won\'t have any difficulty defeating a fighter of this level. Beat one to show me your value.";
D.q[6029] = "";
D.q[4125] = "You seem quite determined, or is it just that you\'re just stubborn?! I like people like you... those who devour Pikokos, bite into life as they would bite into an enemy! We\'re about to leave and live a long adventure! We must be ready. I recently bought a fantastic cannon for my ship, but I\'m lacking ordnance since I used it all to practice on Raul Mops in Cania Bay. Maybe you should go and have a look over there. I\'ll also need arrow heads to fight against Kanniballs. \nBesides, I\'d also like you to bring me back my favourite breakfast: deep fried Kaniger ears in sesame oil!!! If you manage to bring me all of these things, then, and only then, we\'ll be able to leave!";
D.q[6019] = "";
D.q[6011] = "Crocodyl Dandy? Yeah, that\'s me. Did you come to try on my Mopy King fabric g-string?";
D.q[2769] = "You feel ready to pass the level Nidanwa? Perfect! Challenge a fighter of this level to a fair fight. Beat him to prove your value.";
D.q[6020] = "";
D.q[2888] = "Belwlbone! Bilbulubu bu ba bi bobo bu bulbi bi bo....\nBi bu bi bebe ibu ob eb bort be bune.";
D.q[2904] = "Good. If you possess a Kannipiwi cap or a Guava cap, which one gives you most vitality in combat?";
D.q[6021] = "";
D.q[6890] = "You have snatched away my little Bow Meow. What shall I do without him? My life has no meaning, I do not want to sleep alone at night or play with dolls in my corner.";
D.q[6024] = "";
D.q[3234] = "Yeehhaaaaa! Kamas! Kamas!\nDo you want a few?";
D.q[2759] = "To become a Rokwa, you must defeat a disciple of your level in a fair fight, in front of me!\n\nDon\'t forget to wear your outfit!";
D.q[3580] = "You promise help me.";
D.q[6226] = "Calm yourselves... I\'m going to tell you what little I know. When I was working with him I often saw suspicious people passing by, a little like you people, except a little more distinguished. Then he started earning lots of money and paid his way up the rungs of Bonta\'s social ladder. Then I took over my mother\'s business when he decided to move to a better place. Ever since then I only see him on the rare occasion he comes to place an order. That\'s all I know, I swear.";
D.q[6023] = "";
D.q[1946] = "But I...Arrrgh... I\'m finished! *sigh*";
D.q[5307] = "";
D.q[6891] = "You\'re talking nonsense. I\'ve heard that they are looking to hire clowns at the Trool Fair. You should try your luck, I\'m sure you\'ll have no trouble getting a job.";
D.q[1548] = "Circumstances are just right for you... take advantage. Don\'t let this opportunity pass you by!";
D.q[6460] = "Bloody hussy! I know I should have taken her out when I had the chance. Tell me what you want and I\'ll see if I can help you.";
D.q[2761] = "I must take care of the level passage of many others enthusiasts. Try to come back in one hour, at least!";
D.q[6038] = "";
D.q[5308] = "";
D.q[5388] = "";
D.q[3244] = "D-d-do you want to make a packet? Nothing\'s b-b-b-better than becoming a craftsman! And to make a name for yourself, you\'ve got ru...ru...runes!";
D.q[4369] = "You\'ve been completely useless. Why in the world did Amayiro employ such a loser to guard us? I\'ve to say though, we parted ways on good terms, and he did seem to enjoy meeting up again. I really don\'t understand why he did me over like that. As for those bandits, they\'re going to get it bad, believe me! I\'m not staying here, no way! May Sram help us!";
D.q[5317] = "";
D.q[3757] = "Yeah, you got a couple of things I might take... let\'s talk!";
D.q[3494] = "You win, you paxifik.";
D.q[3262] = "Damn! You scared me.\nI donno what\'s got into \'em but I\'ve made twenty whining Iops run away swearin\' they\'d never be mean ever again.\nAt least you\'ve got some guts!\nSee you lah\'er!";
D.q[2700] = "The goddess eye looks upon you... She whispers of a glorious future. You should go see the Dofus receptacle. Then, go see wise Lenald - he lives nearby.";
D.q[2760] = "Apart from the original Pandawushu, how many styles does our martial art include?";
D.q[1649] = "Come here to cool yourself down with one of our tasty ice creams. We have a large choice of flavours. Have a peek at our menu.";
D.q[6893] = "Brrr...";
D.q[1667] = "COME AND TEST YOUR SKILLS! LOADS OF PRIZES TO WIN! Hello there, I\'ve the feeling you\'re handy at those long range shots! I don\'t know if I should let you play... you might win all the prizes! Oh well, I\'ll let you have a go because you look like you\'ll enjoy it! It\'s only 20 Kamas a game.";
D.q[2642] = "I\'m the most popular person on this island, and the most beautiful, and the strongest and I\'m not scared of anything or anybody! Mouahahaha! Hum, excuse me, do you need something?";
D.q[5318] = "";
D.q[6044] = "Danathor is waiting for me, I have to go speak to him about very important things. Spit it out.";
D.q[2940] = "Hmm, I see you have a key to this den... So, I\'m going to let you in. But be careful, I don\'t think my colleagues will go easy on you. The Pandora Master who settled here has recruited the best Pandikazes to protect him. Are you sure you want to come in?";
D.q[7445] = "";
D.q[1660] = "Come herre and admirrre all sorrts of monsterrrs for 10 Kamas only! They\'re all errorrs of Sirr Silvosse, Masterr of naturre, prrobably distrrracted by an evil spirrit!\nKeep your hands off the cages! And stay away frrom them and you might be safe.... hehehe!";
D.q[6451] = "Are you doing it on purpose? When you speak to me, you\'ll address me as Mistress. \'Yes, mistress, no mistress, three bags full mistress\'. Got it?";
D.q[1663] = "Dark Vlad has resurfaced! he\'s now haunting the Evil Forest again!";
D.q[6048] = "";
D.q[4405] = "Ho ho, a Bontarian here in Brakmar? I suppose that the news has even spread to the enemy? \nI really should call the guards to have you skinned alive, but maybe you can fill my pockets a little more, hm?";
D.q[6053] = "";
D.q[1565] = "Darn it, I didn\'t think the militia could search my things. Don\'t you think you should deal with Brakmar instead of annoying people who are trying to do their job.";
D.q[6056] = "";
D.q[53] = "By the Twelve! There was a way in just here, I\'m sure of it. Wasn\'t there? I don\'t understand. I can\'t find it. My father always said I\'d get old one day, and I never believed him.";
D.q[359] = "Boil 75 Acorns, 75 Evil Dandelion Tongues and 70 Rose Petals in a big pot for a few hours. You\'ll get a delicious acorn soup...\nAhh yes, so good.";
D.q[4868] = "Yeah, you\'re telling me! That lazy bloody delivery guy is late. I bet he\'s hanging around fishing and he just hasn\'t seen the time! Hey, could you maybe take this letter too him? I told him to hurry. We can\'t leave our post to tell him oursleves...";
D.q[2840] = "Let\'s see... It seems you\'ve started to train with this brave Amayiro.\nIt might be time for you to choose an order and to specialise in a field to serve best the interests of Bonta!\n\nI\'m part of the Order of the Salvatory Spirit myself. If you wish to know more about another order, I recommend you visit the other floors of the tower...";
D.q[1439] = "Show this poison to Amayiro and tell him you found it near Rimaraf\'s place.\nI wrote the name \'Oni Tnec\' on the proof of purchase.\nIf it doesn\'t work, you can ask Anik Mech to make you a new badge with this name for a so-called confidential mission...";
D.q[4324] = "While we wait for Milone to finish the jewel, we\'ll have to meet our friend Xephires. The Tower of Bonta will be perfect... where you found the piece of paper. Here\'s a letter, do what you must to make sure Xephires receives it. Remember that he spends a lot of time in the Drunken Pandawa Inn... you\'ve probably forgotten already!";
D.q[1228] = "Can\'t you see I\'m on patrol? Get outta here!";
D.q[642] = "So let me sign this little piece of paper... Go and see the Alchemist Examiner. Unfortunately, I don\'t know where he\'s. The only thing I can tell you is that he\'s carrying out research into the calcium of the post-mortem intranasal cartilage.";
D.q[4287] = "We\'re trying to look like merchants, not bloody tramps! You could have asked Amayiro to get us some decent clothes. \nWell, it\'s too late now anyway, we\'ll have to get going. There\'s more guards hidden in the vehicles. They\'ll come help us if we\'re attacked. Let\'s go!";
D.q[6894] = "Purr... purr...";
D.q[5319] = "";
D.q[5455] = "";
D.q[3889] = "s";
D.q[5456] = "";
D.q[6895] = "Brrr... purrpurr...";
D.q[4168] = "Let me warn you! I hate when people make fun of my name, so don\'t even try!\nI guess that you\'re here to use my Scarplane. \nWell, before I let you do that, you must help me.";
D.q[6149] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
